candidates.definition: Attributes describing physical characteristics or configurations of objects and natural features.

positive_examples: The bed has a memory foam mattress with medium firmness.
This washing machine features a front-loading design for easier access.
The grassland shows sparse vegetation coverage across the rolling hills.
The oak tree is cultivated for its valuable timber wood.
The couch cushions are made of high-density foam material.
The dryer loads from the top with a large capacity drum.
negative_examples: The bed costs $500 and is on sale this week.
I prefer using this washing machine because it's energy efficient.
The grassland is located near the highway intersection.
The oak tree was planted in 1985 by the previous owner.
The meeting will be held in the conference room.
The software has many useful features for data analysis.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: TemporalAttribute, LocationAttribute, ValueAttribute, BehavioralAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes that describe characteristics, preparation methods, or qualities of food and beverages.

positive_examples: This coffee has a medium roast and coarse grind.
The restaurant specializes in authentic Italian cuisine.
I prefer my steak cooked medium-rare.
The cheese is aged and has a sharp flavor.
This wine has a full-bodied taste with fruity notes.
The bread is freshly baked and still warm.
negative_examples: The restaurant is located downtown.
The chef graduated from culinary school.
Food prices have increased this year.
The kitchen equipment needs maintenance.
She works as a food critic.
The grocery store closes at 9 PM.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: LocationAttribute, TemporalAttribute, SizeAttribute, ColorAttribute, MaterialAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes that describe qualities, characteristics, or technical properties of media content like music, recordings, or visual material.

positive_examples: This album is classified as progressive rock genre.
The recording was made in stereo with high fidelity.
The photographer used a low-angle shot for dramatic effect.
The sound quality is characterized by crystal clear reproduction.
This compilation album features various artists from the jazz genre.
The recording attributes include the studio location and equipment used.
negative_examples: The book has 300 pages and hardcover binding.
The building is 50 feet tall with brick construction.
She has brown hair and green eyes.
The car has four doors and leather seats.
The recipe calls for two cups of flour.
The relationship between the characters developed slowly.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: PhysicalAttribute, TemporalAttribute, SpatialAttribute, PersonalAttribute, QuantitativeAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes describing financial or economic characteristics, status, or performance of accounts, investments, or entities

positive_examples: The bond received an AAA credit rating from Moody's.
Her savings account has high liquidity but low yield.
The startup's economic role shifted from consumer to producer.
His investment portfolio shows moderate risk attributes.
The account status changed from pending to active.
The mutual fund's performance attributes include diversification and growth potential.
negative_examples: The car's physical attributes include red paint and leather seats.
She has strong leadership qualities and communication skills.
The building's structural attributes meet safety codes.
His personality traits include honesty and reliability.
The software's functional attributes include user interface design.
The patient's medical attributes show normal vital signs.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: PhysicalAttribute, TemporalAttribute, QualityAttribute, SpatialAttribute, CausalAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes that classify objects, materials, or organizations by their industrial, commercial, or technical characteristics.

positive_examples: The pharmaceutical company obtained FDA approval for its new drug.
This steel meets automotive industry grade specifications.
The chemical is classified as a Class 3 flammable liquid for shipping.
The textile manufacturer specializes in organic cotton production.
The software company focuses on enterprise-level security solutions.
These components are rated for aerospace industry standards.
negative_examples: The red car was parked outside the building.
She felt happy about her promotion at work.
The temperature reached 85 degrees yesterday.
The book contains 300 pages of historical information.
He lives in a two-story house with a garden.
The movie lasted for two hours and fifteen minutes.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: PhysicalAttribute, TemporalAttribute, LocationAttribute, QuantityAttribute, QualityAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes that describe the current state or condition of entities in systems, organizations, or processes.

positive_examples: The patient's consciousness level was assessed as alert and responsive.
The server status shows it is currently online and operational.
Her membership status in the organization is active and in good standing.
The endangered species has a conservation status of critically threatened.
My instant messaging status is set to away from keyboard.
The manufacturing process status indicates successful completion.
negative_examples: The building has a height of fifty meters.
She possesses excellent leadership qualities.
The temperature outside is seventy-five degrees.
His relationship to the company is as a consultant.
The car's color is bright red with chrome details.
The document contains sensitive financial information.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: QuantitativeAttribute, QualitativeAttribute, PositionalAttribute, TemporalAttribute

candidates.definition: EnergyAttrs are attributes that characterize energy consumption, efficiency, or power-related properties of systems and devices.

positive_examples: This refrigerator has an Energy Star rating for its low power consumption.
The washing machine displays an A++ energy efficiency class label.
The server system has real-time power monitoring capabilities.
This air conditioner meets European energy efficiency standards.
The device's energy consumption is rated at 50 watts per hour.
The appliance received an energy efficiency certification last year.
negative_examples: This phone has excellent build quality and durability.
The car has a sleek design and comfortable interior.
The software runs smoothly on older hardware.
This material has high tensile strength and flexibility.
The product comes with a two-year warranty.
The device has advanced security features and encryption.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: QualityAttribute, PerformanceAttribute, SecurityAttribute, DesignAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes that characterize legal systems, agents, or politico-economic frameworks within juridical contexts.

positive_examples: The defendant's legal standing in this case is questionable.
This country operates under a common law system.
The corporation acts as a legal entity in contract negotiations.
Federal jurisdiction applies to interstate commerce disputes.
The plaintiff has constitutional rights that must be protected.
Parliamentary democracy defines this nation's governmental structure.
negative_examples: The company's financial performance improved this quarter.
She has excellent communication skills for teamwork.
The building's architectural style is modernist.
His academic credentials include a PhD in chemistry.
The software has user-friendly interface features.
The patient's medical history shows no allergies.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: PhysicalAttribute, TemporalAttribute, SocialAttribute, CognitiveTrait

candidates.definition: Attributes that describe characteristics or qualities of commercial services and hospitality offerings.

positive_examples: The hotel room features a king-size bed and ocean view.
This restaurant offers 24-hour room service to guests.
The spa is currently closed for renovations.
The penthouse suite includes a private balcony and concierge service.
The fitness center is open from 6 AM to 10 PM daily.
The hotel lobby has complimentary WiFi and business center access.
negative_examples: The building has five floors and an elevator.
She has excellent communication skills and leadership experience.
The car's engine is powerful and fuel-efficient.
The software has advanced security features and cloud integration.
His personality is outgoing and friendly.
The city's population is growing rapidly this decade.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: PhysicalAttribute, PersonalAttribute, TemporalAttribute, SpatialAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes and properties specific to software systems, programs, and computing environments.

positive_examples: The application's memory usage exceeded 4GB during peak operation.
The database connection timeout is set to 30 seconds.
This program requires Python version 3.8 or higher to run.
The server's CPU utilization spiked to 95% during the batch job.
The PATH environment variable determines where executables are found.
The software has a maximum file size limit of 100MB.
negative_examples: The car's fuel efficiency is rated at 30 miles per gallon.
The building's height reaches 50 stories above ground level.
The patient's blood pressure measured 120 over 80.
The fabric's thread count is 400 threads per square inch.
The diamond's clarity grade is rated as VS1.
The athlete's running speed averaged 8 minutes per mile.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: PhysicalAttribute, BiologicalAttribute, MechanicalAttribute, ChemicalAttribute

candidates.definition: Attributes that specify quantifiable properties or dimensions being measured in objects or processes.

positive_examples: The length of the table is 6 feet.
Her running speed was quite impressive today.
The width of the doorway needs to be measured.
The car's acceleration rate exceeded expectations.
We need to check the height clearance here.
The volume of this container is 2 liters.
negative_examples: The table is made of oak wood.
She ran gracefully through the park.
The red door stood wide open.
The car belongs to my neighbor.
We walked towards the tall building.
This container holds my favorite snacks.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: QualitativeAttribute, TemporalAttribute, SpatialAttribute, InherentAttribute

candidates.definition: A relational attribute that assigns entities to predefined categories or classes within systematic taxonomies or classification schemes.

positive_examples: The airport was classified as a Category B facility under ICAO standards.
This bacteria tested gram-positive in the laboratory analysis.
France is a member state of the European Union.
The meeting is scheduled for 3 PM Eastern Standard Time.
The statement was marked as true in the logical system.
This investment carries a high-risk rating from the agency.
negative_examples: The building is 50 meters tall and made of concrete.
She has brown eyes and curly hair.
The temperature today reached 85 degrees Fahrenheit.
The package weighs 2.5 pounds and costs fifteen dollars.
His performance improved by 20% over last quarter.
The car can accelerate from 0 to 60 mph in 6 seconds.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: QuantitativeAttribute, PhysicalAttribute, TemporalAttribute, QualitativeAttribute
